{
  "texts": [
    "On the client in the script ClientSendOwnInfo, the predefined broadcast form is filled in every frame and is sent to the server.",
    "All relevant data are held by the own avatar's Char-acterBehaviorController script which is referenced here as MyCharacterBehaviorController.",
    "When sending data, developers can choose between using a 'reliable' and an 'unreliable' channel.",
    "Reliable messages are resent if the receiver does not confirm receiving the message (e.g., due to network packet loss).",
    "This technique is appropriate when sending messages which are sent rarely and/or trigger specific decisions such as the assignment to a specific seat on the table by the server."
  ]
}